| footer = [[Ash Wednesday]] and [[Good Friday]] are two days within the Christian penitential season of [[Lent]] that are popular days for churchgoing. The image on the left depicts a [[Lutheran]] [[Divine Service (Lutheran)|Divine Service]] on Ash Wednesday while the image on the right depicts a [[Roman Catholic]] Good Friday service.<ref>{{cite book|title=The Living Church, Volume 138|year=1959|publisher=Morehouse-Gorham Company|language=English|page=221|quote=Case after case was noted where parish church attendance had doubled, tripled, and in some cases, quadrupled at all services on Ash Wednesday. As the weeks of Lent rolled along, reports continued to come in mentioning that attendance at all services during Lent was far greater than at any other period during many of the churches' histories.}}</ref>
