[[Image:BonkerLightened.jpg|thumb|A sex swing]] A '''sex swing''' (also known as a '''sling''') is a type of [[:wikt:harness|harness]] designed to allow [[sexual intercourse]] between one partner suspended by the swing and another who moves freely. <ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.kinkly.com/definition/208/sex-sling | title=What does Sex Sling mean | accessdate=7 September 2016}}</ref>Though there is considerable variety in the design, the most common sex swings have a support for the back, another for the [[buttocks]], and [[stirrup]]s for each leg, which can be adjusted whilst the user is suspended. <ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.thenation.com/article/what-the-pathetic-case-against-rentboy-com-says-about-sex-work/ | title=What the Pathetic Case Against Rentboy.com Says About Sex Work | accessdate=7 September 2016}}</ref>
The following types of sex swing exist: traditional swing, door swing, body swing, and fantasy swing.{{Citation needed|date=January 2016}} The body swing is suspended from one partner's body.{{Citation needed|date=January 2016}} The door swing is mounted on a door.<ref name="PassionShop How To">{{cite web|url=http://www.passionshop.com/blog/sex-toys/how-to-use-a-sex-swing |title=Archived copy |accessdate=January 28, 2016 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150514085912/http://www.passionshop.com/blog/sex-toys/how-to-use-a-sex-swing/ |archivedate=May 14, 2015 }}</ref> The fantasy swing is suspended from an [[eye bolt]] in the ceiling.{{Citation needed|date=January 2016}} In popular culture, sex swing is mostly associated with [[BDSM]] practices. <ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2014/12/20/dungeons-and-genital-clamps-inside-a-legendary-bdsm-chateau.html | title=Dungeons and Genital Clamps: Inside a Legendary BDSM Chateau | accessdate=7 September 2016}}</ref>
==Description==
[[File:Sling.jpg|thumb|[[Hammock]]-style sling for sexual activity]] A sex swing or sling is designed to assist in [[Human sexuality|sexual]] activity.<ref name="PassionShop How To"/> Materials for constructing these devices include [[nylon]] [[webbing]],{{Citation needed|date=January 2016}} heavy [[canvas]],{{Citation needed|date=January 2016}} [[leather]],{{Citation needed|date=January 2016}} [[neoprene]],{{Citation needed|date=January 2016}} heavy [[natural rubber|rubber]],{{Citation needed|date=January 2016}} [[wood]],{{Citation needed|date=January 2016}}and [[steel]].{{Citation needed|date=January 2016}} The designs provide access to the passive (receptive) partner's [[Sex organ|genitalia]], [[perineum]], buttocks, and [[Anus|anal]] areas while supporting the individual in a comfortable position, with the hips flexed, to allowing the passive partner to fully relax.{{Citation needed|date=January 2016}}
The most common sex swing is similar to a [[hammock]] and holds the receptive partner in a [[supine position]] (back down).{{Citation needed|date=January 2016}} A variant of the hammock style is a hanging platform of wood or metal, padded for comfort, on which the receptive partner reclines.{{Citation needed|date=January 2016}} The hanging platform differs from the hammock style in that, being rigid, the receptive partner's back is straight rather than bowed.{{Citation needed|date=January 2016}} Both the hammock and hanging platform designs are often equipped with loops or stirrups to support the ankles or calves up without the requiring exertion by the receptive partner.{{Citation needed|date=January 2016}} This allows the receptive partner's hips to be flexed without exertion, improving access to the areas of interest.{{Citation needed|date=January 2016}}
Hammock-style swings vary in the number of suspension points from three (two at the hips and one at the head), to four (two at the hips and two at the shoulders), to five (two each at hips and shoulders, plus one at the head).{{Citation needed|date=January 2016}} The functional difference between these variants lies in the stability of the sling when in use: the more suspension points, the less movement.{{Citation needed|date=January 2016}} However, many users prefer to have a greater range of movement.{{Citation needed|date=January 2016}}
Another variation is the sit swing, which holds the receptive partner upright in sitting position, rather than supine.{{Citation needed|date=January 2016}} Sit swings take most of the body's weight with large padded loops around the thighs, or some similar arrangement.{{Citation needed|date=January 2016}} Sit swings are commonly suspended from a single point attached to the ceiling, to a free-standing sex swing stand, or a door.{{Citation needed|date=January 2016}} Door swings offer quicker installation and lower cost, but sacrifice some flexibility.{{Citation needed|date=January 2016}}
== Purpose ==
The main purpose of sex swings is to make sexual intercourse more exciting and effortless. A sex swing may enable greater freedom of movement during intercourse or assist with challenging [[sex position]]s.<ref name="PassionShop How To"/> Swings may be used for [[Vaginal sex|vaginal]] and [[Anal sex|anal]] sex, [[fellatio]], and [[cunnilingus]].
Sex swings can enable individuals with a physical impairment or [[disability]] to enjoy a wide range of sexual activities. Individuals with muscular weakness or [[arthritis]] may use a sex swing to reduce the strain on affected muscles or joints.{{Citation needed|date=January 2016}} Individuals who use a [[wheelchair]] can engage in sexual activity using a sex swing suspended from a [[hoist (device)|hoist]].<ref name="Wheelchair Sex Swing">{{cite web |url=http://www.streetsie.com/wheelchair-hoist-sex-swing |title=Wheelchair Hoist Sex Swing Make Disability Sex Easy |work=streetsie.com |access-date=February 18, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120119040046/http://www.streetsie.com/wheelchair-hoist-sex-swing |archive-date=January 19, 2012 |dead-url=yes}}{{better source|date=March 2016}} Note: This source is judged unreliable, as it states Wikipedia as a source.</ref>{{better source|date=March 2016}} <!-- This source is a circular reference, citing Wikipedia as a source. -->
== Safety ==
It is important to follow the provided instructions when using a sex swing. Secure mounting is vital to avoid injury to the suspended partner from falling. The use of [[toggle bolt]]s, such as would be used to hang a dreamcatcher, is not appropriate. Installing springs, if supplied, is important to reduce physical [[Shock (mechanics)|shock]] to the suspended partner caused by rapid [[deceleration]] when bouncing in a sex swing.<ref>{{cite web |title=Sex Swing Springs Are NOT Just for Suspension |url=http://www.sexswing.info/sex-swing-springs-are-not-just-for-suspension |work=sexswing.info |access-date=February 18, 2016 |first=Abby |last=Woods}}{{better source|date=March 2016}}</ref>{{better source|date=March 2016}}
